.TH VEK_DOT_B1 3 "2024-01-01" "vek 0.8.0" "Library Functions Manual"
.SH NAME
vek_dot_b1 \- binary dot product (popcount of AND)
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <vek.h>
.sp
.BI "size_t vek_dot_b1(const uint8_t *" a ", const uint8_t *" b ", size_t " n ");"
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
.BR vek_dot_b1 ()
computes the dot product of two binary vectors packed into uint8 arrays.
This is equivalent to the population count (popcount) of the bitwise AND
of corresponding bytes:
.PP
.RS
result = popcount(a[i] & b[i]) for i = 0 to n-1
.RE
.PP
Each bit in the input vectors represents a binary value (0 or 1).
.SH PARAMETERS
.TP
.I a
First input binary vector packed into uint8 bytes. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I b
Second input binary vector packed into uint8 bytes. Must have at least
.I n
elements.
.TP
.I n
Number of uint8 elements (not bits). Must be greater than 0.
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns the number of matching set bits as a
.BR size_t .
.SH EXAMPLES
.nf
uint8_t a[] = {0xFF, 0x0F};  // 11111111 00001111
uint8_t b[] = {0x0F, 0xFF};  // 00001111 11111111
size_t result = vek_dot_b1(a, b, 2);  // 12 (8 + 4)
.fi
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR vek_hamming_b1 (3),
.BR vek_cosine_b1 (3),
.BR vek_dot_u8 (3)
